  </CaptionedBlock>

  <div id="trust" class="scroll-mt-40">
    <DefBox
      term="Buying safely: verify any pet shop's AVS licence first"
      definition="Every legitimate pet shop in Singapore is listed on the AVS public registry of licensed pet shops. Search the shop's name or licence number before paying any deposit, to anyone; if a seller isn't on the registry, they aren't licensed, whatever the listing claims."
      bridge="Curious Tails holds AVS pet shop licence AS24J00046. Check us first; an honest shop won't mind, and a genuine seller never will. Rare breeds like the Havanese attract grey-market imports precisely because local litters are scarce, and puppies sold outside licensed channels are often smuggled without vaccination; buyers have been fined $7,000 for unknowingly purchasing one."
